OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1773245483
OL,3,CGlasgow Central remains closed after
OL,4,Chuge fire nearby
OL,6,FThe rail infrastructure organisation
OL,7,Fsaid it recognised the inconvenience
OL,8,Ffor passengers, but it had to wait
OL,9,Funtil building assessment work was
OL,10,Fcompleted.
OL,12,FThe fire began in a vape shop on Union
OL,13,FStreet at about 15:45 on Sunday,
OL,14,Fbefore flames quickly spread through
OL,15,Fthe building and around the corner
OL,16,Fonto Gordon Street.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1773245483
OL,3,CGlasgow Central remains closed after
OL,4,Chuge fire nearby
OL,6,FWhile Central Station itself has
OL,7,Fescaped major damage, the impact of
OL,8,Fthe firefighting efforts and the
OL,9,Fintense heat of the blaze means that
OL,10,Ffurther assessment is required.
OL,12,FNetwork Rail Route director Ross Moran
OL,13,Fsaid: "We are grateful to Scottish
OL,14,FFire and Rescue teams who have been
OL,15,Fworking tirelessly to contain the fire
OL,16,Fon the Union Corner site.
OL,18,F"I am pleased to advise passengers
OL,19,Fthat we will be able to open Glasgow
OL,20,FCentral low-level station from
OL,21,Ftomorrow morning (Wednesday).
OL,26,@uD@GOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
